The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma recently in Beitbridge
AMAVIANO (combination of Venda and Amapiano) musician Bhadilah continues to shine in the fast-growing border town of Beitbridge as he on Saturday, was recognised as one of the best entertainers in the town. The artiste was honoured by organisers of the Beitbridge Business Expo for being the Best Entertainer. The Beitbridge Business Expo second edition was held at Dulivhadzimu Stadium to promote investment and the town’s economic growth.  The programme, which started last Thursday and ended on Saturday, was held under the theme: “Beitbridge 24 seven”. Bhadilah, through his extensive musical career which has seen him become a regional brand, was recognised for his efforts. The artiste, who recently launched a clothing label, said he is elated that his works continue to be appreciated. <img class="wp-image-619735 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Bhadilah-3.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Bhadilah-3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Bhadilah-3-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Bhadilah “I feel honoured for being recognised as the best entertainer in my hometown. This shows that I’m moving in the right direction. I’m really grateful for this award and it has given me the zeal to work harder in pushing my brand, the town of Beitbridge and the Southern African region at large,” said Bhadilah. He said his focus now is on producing more visuals. “I’m looking forward to recording a series of music videos for my previous tracks. I also intend to connect with South African acts for collaborations on shows and in the studio.” – @mthabisi_mthire